place.name: STOCKLINCH
place.gazetteerText: STOCKLINCH-MAGDALEN, a parish in Chard district, Somerset; 2½ miles NE by N of Ilminster, and 6 WSW of Martock r. station. Post town, Ilminster. Acres, 199. Rated property, £500. Pop., 116. Houses, 27. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £140. Patron, the Rev.J. Allen. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
